============================================================

Written the improvement plan to `tools/title-loop/docs/25-2331e30/improvement-plan.md`.

**Summary of the plan:**

The single failure is `DAT FLATBREADS` (an OCR artifact from a previous page) being selected over `FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS` in a compound title. The plan proposes two complementary fixes:

1. **Vocabulary corroboration** — When assembling multi-title output (≥2 ALL_CAPS candidates), check that each candidate's content words (≥4 letters) appear elsewhere in the document. `DAT` appears nowhere else → rejected. `FINNISH`, `MILK`, `POTATO` all appear in recipe bodies → kept. For short candidates (≤3 content words), require 100% corroboration.

2. **Improved preamble detection** — When `findBurstEnd` finishes skipping garbled lines and the next line is a short ALL_CAPS fragment followed by lowercase body text, skip it too. This prevents `DAT FLATBREADS` from entering the candidate pool at all.

Both fixes are targeted and low-risk — corroboration only applies in the multi-title path, and preamble detection only fires after garbled text has already been detected.
