{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DbJ7XqUzVuU5SFn3Afaxcu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Iteration 24 Code Review\n     2→\n     3→## Files Reviewed\n     4→\n     5→- `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` — all uncommitted changes\n     6→- `lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts` — new file\n     7→\n     8→## Summary of Changes\n     9→\n    10→The iteration implements 7 improvement categories from the improvement plan:\n    11→\n    12→1. **Dictionary-guided OCR repair** (`repairOcrWord`, `repairOcrText`, `generateSubstitutions`) — new functions that resolve ambiguous OCR digit→letter substitutions using a food-word dictionary. Applied before candidate scoring in `buildCandidates` and again in `normalizeOcrTitle`.\n    13→\n    14→2. **Food dictionary** (`food-dictionary.ts`) — ~500 English and Polish food/cooking words stored as a `Set<string>` without diacritics.\n    15→\n    16→3. **Candidate-relative position bonus** — position factor now uses `candidateIndex / rawScored.length` instead of `rs.position / lines.length`, so filtered preamble lines don't penalize the first surviving candidate.\n    17→\n    18→4. **First-after-preamble bonus** (+0.08) — when all lines before the first candidate are empty or fail hard filters, that candidate gets an explicit structural-title-position boost.\n    19→\n    20→5. **Title-absent page detection** (`isTitleAbsentPage`) — returns empty when the first 3 non-empty lines are all ingredients/instructions, with rawScore and position guards.\n    21→\n    22→6. **Compound title dedup protection** — titles containing ` + `, ` : `, or ` & ` are protected from the shorter-substring dedup filter.\n    23→\n    24→7. **Expanded garbled-text detection** — pipe-in-word and mixed Cyrillic/Latin checks in `isLikelyGarbled`.\n    25→\n    26→8. **Expanded cooking verbs** — `COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` grew from ~32 to ~80 verbs.\n    27→\n    28→9. **Bilingual layout boost** — detects [FoodName]\\n[Translation]\\n...[Section label] pattern and boosts position-0 candidate.\n    29→\n    30→10. **New hard filters** — `MAIN RECIPE:` prefix and `--` sub-section headers added to `METADATA_PATTERNS`.\n    31→\n    32→## Correctness vs. Improvement Plan\n    33→\n    34→All 11 changes listed in the plan's summary table are implemented. The code matches the plan's intent.\n    35→\n    36→**Critical constraint verified**: The substring deduplication block (\"keep the shorter\") is untouched. The compound-title guard is a short-circuit `return true` inserted *before* the existing logic — it prevents compound titles from entering the dedup, but does not alter the dedup logic itself.\n    37→\n    38→## Issues Found and Fixed\n    39→\n    40→### 1. Array notation (AGENTS.md violation) — Fixed\n    41→\n    42→Several new declarations used `T[]` instead of `Array<T>`:\n    43→- `positions: { index: number; replacements: string[] }[]`\n    44→- `generateSubstitutions` return type and parameter\n    45→- `isTitleAbsentPage(lines: string[])`\n    46→\n    47→All converted to `Array<T>` notation.\n    48→\n    49→### 2. Redundant `--` pattern in `passesHardFilters` — Fixed\n    50→\n    51→The pattern `/^--\\s*\\w/` was added to both `METADATA_PATTERNS` (checked via `looksLikeMetadata()`) and directly in `passesHardFilters`. Since `passesHardFilters` already calls `looksLikeMetadata()`, the direct check was redundant. Removed the duplicate from `passesHardFilters`.\n    52→\n    53→## Minor Observations (Not Fixed — Low Priority)\n    54→\n    55→- **`OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN`** matches all digits 0-9 but `OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS` only has entries for 0, 1, 4, 5. Words containing only digits 2, 3, 6-9 will trigger `repairOcrWord` but exit via the `positions.length === 0` early return. Not a bug — just a micro-inefficiency for rare cases.\n    56→\n    57→- **Double OCR repair**: `repairOcrText` runs in `buildCandidates` (pre-scoring) and again in `normalizeOcrTitle` (post-selection). The second pass is a no-op for already-repaired words (the artifact pattern won't match), so it's safe but slightly wasteful.\n    58→\n    59→## Pre-existing Issues (Not Regressions)\n    60→\n    61→CLI results show 2 cases that don't match expectations — verified against the committed (pre-change) version:\n    62→\n    63→- **Faszerowana papryka**: extracts \"Faszerowana papryka PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM 파프리카 계란찜\" (appends Korean transliteration) — pre-existing\n    64→- **FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS**: extracts \"DAT FLATBREADS + FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS\" (truncated prefix) — pre-existing\n    65→\n    66→## Test Results\n    67→\n    68→- **Unit tests**: 33/33 passed\n    69→- **CLI smoke test**: all 11 real input files processed, outputs consistent with pre-change baseline\n    70→\n    71→## Architecture Assessment\n    72→\n    73→The changes are well-structured:\n    74→- New OCR repair functions are pure, stateless, and isolated — easy to test independently\n    75→- The food dictionary is a separate module with a clear boundary\n    76→- Each improvement plan item maps to a discrete, localized code change\n    77→- No global behavioral changes that could cause unexpected regressions in unrelated cases\n    78→\n    79→## Performance Assessment\n    80→\n    81→- Dictionary lookup uses a `Set` (O(1) per lookup)\n    82→- `generateSubstitutions` is bounded at 8 positions × 2 replacements max = 256 variants worst case; typical recipe words have 0-2 OCR artifacts = 1-4 variants\n    83→- `repairOcrText` adds one pass per candidate (~20-40 candidates typical) with short-circuit on words without artifacts\n    84→- `isTitleAbsentPage` scans first 3 non-empty lines — negligible cost\n    85→- Overall: well within the 10-second mobile constraint. The embedding model call remains the dominant cost.\n    86→\n    87→## Overall Assessment\n    88→\n    89→Solid implementation that closely follows the improvement plan. Code is clean, changes are localized, and no regressions were introduced. Two minor style/redundancy issues were fixed during review.\n    90→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015ygKBPCmwC1T2xezVmc3V5","session_id":"93fcd165-c384-4cf1-b48c-241fa9498df5","uuid":"5223e7f7-0120-4ad5-8b13-cae6631bb654"}
