{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018ueNRHCygGLcmmzQA2fZKw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Title Extraction Implementation Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the title extraction pipeline in the Fasola project. Here's the complete technical breakdown:\n\n### 1. FULL PIPELINE ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Overall Flow:**\n```\nOCR Text Input\n  ↓\nbuildCandidates() [single + 2-line + 3-line joins]\n  ↓\nHard filters (length, ingredients, metadata, garbled, etc.)\n  ↓\nPass 1: Embed candidates & compute rawScore\n  ↓\nPass 2: Apply bonuses (position, ALL_CAPS, structural)\n  ↓\nPre-threshold bilingual detection\n  ↓\nThreshold filtering\n  ↓\nMulti-title guards & deduplication\n  ↓\nFinal selection (max 3 titles)\n  ↓\nOCR normalization & return\n```\n\n### 2. CANDIDATE GENERATION (`buildCandidates` - lines 441-605)\n\n**Pre-processing steps:**\n1. **Burst end detection** (lines 355-410): Skips initial garbled/short lines, prose preambles, and overflow markers\n2. **Hyphen-broken line joining**: Reconstructs lines split with trailing `-`\n3. **Short ALL_CAPS coalescing** (lines 465-508): Merges consecutive ALL_CAPS lines (≤2 words, ≤25 chars each) into single candidates (handles OCR fragmentation like \"LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS\")\n4. **Continuation line pre-merging** (lines 510-528): Merges lines starting with `/&+:(` into preceding line before candidate generation (handles \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\")\n\n**Candidate types generated:**\n- **Single**: Individual lines passing hard filters\n- **2-line**: Two consecutive non-empty lines joined (blocked if first is section label AND ≤2 words)\n- **3-line**: Three consecutive non-empty lines joined (same blocking rules)\n\n**Pre-filter to 25 candidates** (lines 590-602): Prioritizes ALL_CAPS, then short candidates (≤5 words)\n\n### 3. HARD FILTERS (`passesHardFilters` - lines 308-349)\n\nLines **must** pass ALL these checks:\n- **Length**: 3-80 characters\n- **Ingredient check**: No measurement patterns (cups, tbsp, g, ml, łyżka, etc.) and no \"to taste\" / \"do smaku\"\n- **Number start**: No lines starting with digits (with optional bullet)\n- **Metadata**: No serving sizes, prep times, categories, corrupted OCR serving (DLA patterns)\n- **Garbled**: Fails if suspicious (see `isLikelyGarbled` below)\n- **Cooking instruction**: No lines starting with cooking verbs (beat, fold, stir, bake, etc. + Polish equivalents like smaż, gotuj, pokrój)\n- **Pipe/slash/breadcrumbs**: No \" | \" or 2+ \"/\" (single \"/\" OK for \"TITLE / SUBTITLE\")\n- **Trailing page numbers**: No excessive spaces + digits\n- **Bullets**: No `[-•*]` prefixes\n- **Section headers**: No \"For the sauce:\", no trailing \":\" (unless \" : \" separator)\n- **Page references**: No \"Page N\" or \"Strona N\"\n- **Category tags**: No `[TAGS]`\n- **Section labels**: Not in SECTION_LABELS set (~100 labels in Polish/English)\n- **Single-word fragments**: No non-title words (the, and, for, but, etc.)\n- **Word count**: Max 7 words (or 8+ with separators: +, :, &, /)\n\n### 4. GARBLED TEXT DETECTION (`isLikelyGarbled` - lines 209-275)\n\nReturns TRUE (garbled) if:\n1. Fewer than 2 letters\n2. Pipe embedded in words: `[a-z]\\|[a-z]` (OCR artifact like \"Sp|aszcz\")\n3. Mixed Latin + Cyrillic (OCR corruption)\n4. Vowel ratio: < 10% or > 85% (English/Polish text is typically 30-50%)\n5. Single orphaned word ≤3 Unicode letters not in COMMON_SHORT set\n6. Single word with lowercase→uppercase transition (e.g., \"UuIw\", \"aBC\")\n7. Starts with lowercase letter (recipe titles never do)\n8. Mid-text sentence boundary: \". \" followed by letter (except if ends with \")\")\n9. Multi-word with garbled short lowercase word (≤2 letters, not in extended common-short set)\n\n### 5. EMBEDDING MODEL & SIMILARITY\n\n**Model:** `Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (Hugging Face transformers.js)\n- 384-dimensional embeddings\n- Pre-normalized (L2) so cosine similarity = dot product\n- See `/lib/text-classifier/embedder.ts`\n\n**Reference embeddings:**\n- `TITLE_REFERENCE`: \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\"\n- `HEADER_REFERENCE`: \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\"\n- `NOISE_REFERENCE`: \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\"\n\n**Similarity computation** (`cosineSimilarity` - embeddings.ts:30-38):\n```typescript\nfunction cosineSimilarity(e1: Array<number>, e2: Array<number>): number {\n  let dotProduct = 0;\n  for (let i = 0; i < e1.length; i++) {\n    dotProduct += e1[i] * e2[i];\n  }\n  return dotProduct; // Already normalized\n}\n```\n\n### 6. HEURISTIC SCORING SYSTEM (Pass 1-2, lines 824-937)\n\n#### Pass 1: Raw Score\n```\nrawScore = titleSim - max(headerSim, noiseSim)\n```\n- Quantifies how much more title-like than header/noise a candidate is\n- Can be negative (strong header/noise signal)\n\n#### Pass 2: Bonuses Applied\n\n**a) Position factor** (lines 892-895):\n- Multiplicative only (doesn't replace rawScore, amplifies signal)\n- Early candidates (relative position < 0.5): bonus factor = 1.0 + 0.12 × (1 - 2×relPos)\n- Later candidates: factor = 1.0\n- Effect: first candidate gets ~12% boost, fades to neutral at midpoint\n\n**b) ALL_CAPS bonus** (lines 900-902):\n- 2+ word ALL_CAPS: +0.08\n- 1-word ALL_CAPS: +0.03 (single words are usually section labels, not titles)\n- 0 bonus for mixed-case\n\n**c) Structural heading bonus** (lines 904-905):\n- ALL_CAPS ≥2 words where each significant word has ≥4 alpha letters: +0.10\n- Only applied to `firstStructuralHeading` (best structural candidate by rawScore)\n- Distinguishes \"AROMATIC SPICE MIX\" (title) from \"INGREDIENTS\" (header)\n\n**d) First-after-preamble bonus** (lines 920-937):\n- If all preceding lines were filtered/empty, first candidate gets +0.08\n- Handles cases like \"FISH & SEAFOOD\\nHalibut with Saffron...\" where section label is filtered\n\n**Score calculation:**\n```\nbaseScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus\nscore = rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus\nthresholdScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus (excludes structural to avoid inflating threshold)\n```\n\n**Structural heading selection** (lines 815-870):\n- Finds ALL_CAPS candidates with ≥2 words, all significant words ≥4 alpha letters\n- Penalizes truncated words (if \"FRON\" + \"SAFFRON\" present, \"FRON\" gets -1.0)\n- Picks best by rawScore, with tiebreakers: single-line > multi-line, more words, earlier position\n\n### 7. SPECIAL BILINGUAL HANDLING\n\n**Method 1: Embedding similarity** (lines 950-963):\n- Detects mixed-case candidate at position 0 + nearby (pos 1-2) ALL_CAPS\n- If similarity > 0.4, treats ALL_CAPS as translation → suppresses for threshold\n\n**Method 2: Layout-based fallback** (lines 965-978):\n- Mixed-case ≥2 words at pos 0 + ALL_CAPS ≥2 words at pos 1-2 with **no shared words**\n- Cross-lingual detection (e.g., Polish + Korean romanization)\n\n**Also handles:**\n- **Subtitle suppression** (lines 1026-1039): Short title at pos 0 + longer mixed-case at pos 1-2 → penalize longer by -0.15\n- **Mixed-case bilingual boost** (lines 1041-1080): Detects foreign name + English translation layout → boosts pos-0 by +0.15\n\n### 8. FILTERING & THRESHOLD\n\n**Threshold calculation** (lines 1082-1085):\n```\nbestThresholdScore = max(thresholdScore of candidates passing bilingual suppression)\nthreshold = max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7)\n```\n- Never below 0.08\n- Uses `thresholdScore` (excludes structural bonus) so bonus doesn't inflate threshold\n\n**Title-absent page guard** (lines 1106-1114):\n- When first 3 non-empty lines are all ingredients/instructions, require rawScore ≥ 0.10 and position ≤ 2\n- Prevents picking stray body text on pages with no title\n\n**Empty-pool fallback** (lines 1090-1104):\n- If no candidates clear threshold, pick first candidate if position ≤ 2 and rawScore > -0.05 (relaxed for early positions)\n- Or if position > 2, require rawScore > 0.02\n\n### 9. DEDUPLICATION & MULTI-TITLE LOGIC (lines 1116-1314)\n\n**Prefix removal** (lines 1116-1131):\n- Removes word-boundary prefixes of structural heading if heading itself survived\n- Examples:\n  - \"ARAYES\" removed when \"ARAYES SHRAK\" survives\n  - \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" alone removed when continued join survives\n\n**Continuation join protection** (lines 1133-1165):\n- Removes single-line versions of multi-line joins starting with `/&+:(`\n- Prevents \"& Coriander\" from destroying \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\"\n\n**Sub-section header filter** (lines 1167-1188):\n- Removes ALL_CAPS candidates followed by ingredient-like content if a longer candidate contains it\n- Example: \"CHLEBEK\" (substring of \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\") is filtered\n\n**Multi-line join protection** (lines 1190-1208):\n- When 2+ candidate words of a join appear as separate singles → remove the singles\n\n**Position-0 compound protection** (lines 1210-1226):\n- Removes distant candidates (>10 lines away) that are substrings of position-0 compound title\n\n**Deduplication rule** (lines 1228-1243):\n```\nKeep if:\n1. No other candidate contains it as substring AND is longer\n2. OR it's a compound title (has \" +\", \" :\", or \" & \" separator)\n```\nShorter wins when there's substring inclusion\n\n**Multi-title logic** (lines 1245-1314):\n```\nif ≥2 ALL_CAPS survivors:\n  if non-first are sub-headers (followed by ingredients) → keep only first\n  else → keep all ALL_CAPS (multi-recipe page)\nelse if 1 ALL_CAPS survivor:\n  if in last 25% of document → pick best earlier mixed-case (likely footer)\n  else → use the ALL_CAPS\nelse (0 ALL_CAPS):\n  if all survivors within 10 lines → keep all (genuine multi-recipe)\n  if span > 10 lines → collapse to one (body-text leakage)\n```\n\n**Final cap:** Up to 3 titles, sorted by document position\n\n### 10. OCR NORMALIZATION (lines 698-775)\n\n**Dictionary-guided OCR repair** (lines 647-675):\n- Maps digits to letters: 0→o, 1→i/l, 4→a, 5→s, ¡→i, €→e\n- Uses FOOD_DICTIONARY (~500 words) to resolve ambiguous substitutions\n- Generates all substitution variants and picks matches\n\n**Post-processing** (lines 721-775):\n1. Dictionary repair first\n2. Strip trailing section markers: `+ SERVING AND STORAGE:` → remove\n3. Character substitution (context-aware for ALL_CAPS vs mixed-case)\n4. Title-case conversion ONLY when substitution changed text (preserves clean ALL_CAPS)\n\n**Title-case function** (lines 611-625):\n- Lowercases small words: a, an, the, and, but, or, in, on, at, to, of, with, from\n- Polish: z, w, i, ze, na, do, od, za, po\n- First word always capitalized\n\n### 11. TEST FIXTURE STRUCTURE\n\n**Files in `/tools/title-loop/input/`:**\n- `{RecipeTitle}.real.txt`: Real OCR from recipe books (ground truth)\n- `{RecipeTitle}.generated.txt`: Synthetic OCR for coverage\n\n**Expected titles extracted from filenames:**\n- Strip `.real.txt` or `.generated.txt` suffix\n- Example: `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander.real.txt` → expected = `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander`\n\n**Multi-title syntax:**\n- Expected format: `Title1 + Title2` (space + plus + space)\n- Extracted format must contain all parts after normalization\n\n**Matching logic** (`titles_match` - lines 169-183):\n```\n1. Normalize both extracted & expected:\n   - NFC Unicode form\n   - Strip NBSP & BOM\n   - Lowercase\n   - Replace hyphens with spaces\n   - Normalize whitespace\n2. OCR substitution: 0→o, 1→i, €→e\n3. Strip Polish diacritics: ąćęłńóśźż → acelnosz\n4. For multi-title (expected with \"+\"):\n   - Split by \"+\", normalize each part\n   - Check if each part is SUBSTRING of extracted_norm\n   All parts must match\n```\n\n### 12. FOOD DICTIONARY CONTENTS\n\n~500 food-related words (no diacritics for OCR resilience):\n- **Proteins**: chicken, beef, salmon, shrimp, tofu, tempeh\n- **Grains**: rice, pasta, bread, flour, quinoa, couscous\n- **Dairy**: butter, cheese, cream, milk, yogurt\n- **Vegetables**: garlic, tomato, potato, carrot, broccoli, mushroom\n- **Fruits**: lemon, apple, berry, mango, pineapple\n- **Spices**: ginger, cinnamon, paprika, basil, oregano, saffron\n- **Cooking terms**: bake, roast, grill, fry, sauté, simmer\n- **Dish types**: salad, soup, stew, pizza, pasta, cake, dessert\n- **Polish entries**: kurczak, wolowina, ser, makaron, placki, pierogi\n\n### 13. TFIDF CLASSIFICATION (for tags, separate from title extraction)\n\nUsed for semantic tag classification (seasons, cuisines, categories), not titles:\n- **IDF formula**: `log(totalLabels / labelsContainingKeyword)`\n- **Score**: Normalized TF × IDF\n- **Threshold**: 0.2 for suggestion inclusion\n- **Similarity threshold** (embeddings.ts): 0.453\n\nLabels include:\n- **Seasons**: whole_year, spring, summer, autumn, winter (Polish equivalents included)\n- **Cuisines**: ~50 (italian, french, polish, indian, thai, korean, mexican, etc.)\n- **Categories**: ~12 (appetizer, soup, salad, pasta, pizza, rice, stew, roast, grill, baked, pastry, dessert, beverage, preserves)\n\n### 14. KEY FILES\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` | Main extraction engine (1361 lines) |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/embedder.ts` | MiniLM model loading & embedding |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/embeddings.ts` | Cosine similarity & embedding classification |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts` | ~500 food words for OCR repair |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/labels.ts` | Season/cuisine/category label definitions |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/tfidf.ts` | TF-IDF tag classification |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts` | 30+ test cases (379 lines) |\n| `/tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts` | CLI wrapper for title extraction |\n| `/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py` | Self-improving iteration loop |\n| `/tools/title-loop/input/` | Test fixtures (~100+ recipes) |\n| `/tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt` | Accuracy tracking log |\n\n### 15. CURRENT ACCURACY TRACKING\n\nFrom `iter.txt`:\n- Iteration 1: 16.7%, Iteration 2: 16.7%, ... Iteration 13: 98.1%\n- Iteration 24: 83.8% (combined: 83.8%, real: 100.0%)\n- Iteration 25: 90.9%\n- Uses separate tracking for \"real\" (actual OCR) vs \"generated\" (synthetic OCR) files\n\n### 16. CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION NOTES\n\n**Immutable deduplication logic** (line 1229):\n```\n// DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" 5 times.\n// The tests require shorter wins.\n```\n\n**Structural heading detection** (lines 815-822):\n- Requires ≥2 words AND each significant word ≥4 alpha letters\n- Filters insignificant tokens (/, &, +, :, D))\n\n**Pre-filtering** (lines 533-542):\n- Removes metadata continuation fragments (short ALL_CAPS immediately after metadata)\n- Prevents \"N\" after \"SERVES 4\" from becoming a candidate\n\n**Truncation penalization** (lines 839-854):\n- Discards truncated OCR words with -1.0 rawScore\n- Example: \"FRON\" penalized if \"SAFFRON\" exists\n\nThis comprehensive system balances rule-based heuristics with semantic embeddings to handle real OCR artifacts while avoiding common pitfalls on mobile platforms."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4855e5db6c6b42e8 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 143420\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 97655</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"93fcd165-c384-4cf1-b48c-241fa9498df5","uuid":"e9e6159c-6f26-407a-8dec-879dc6613ea6","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the title extraction implementation thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The full pipeline: how candidates are generated, scored, filtered, and selected\n2. The embedding model and similarity logic\n3. All heuristic scoring factors\n4. How the test fixtures/ground truth data is structured\n\nSearch in:\n- lib/text-classifier/ - all files related to title extraction\n- Any embedding or similarity related code\n- Test files for title extraction\n- tools/title-loop/ - the loop tooling structure\n\nBe very thorough - read full file contents of key files.","agentId":"a4855e5db6c6b42e8","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Title Extraction Implementation Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the title extraction pipeline in the Fasola project. Here's the complete technical breakdown:\n\n### 1. FULL PIPELINE ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Overall Flow:**\n```\nOCR Text Input\n  ↓\nbuildCandidates() [single + 2-line + 3-line joins]\n  ↓\nHard filters (length, ingredients, metadata, garbled, etc.)\n  ↓\nPass 1: Embed candidates & compute rawScore\n  ↓\nPass 2: Apply bonuses (position, ALL_CAPS, structural)\n  ↓\nPre-threshold bilingual detection\n  ↓\nThreshold filtering\n  ↓\nMulti-title guards & deduplication\n  ↓\nFinal selection (max 3 titles)\n  ↓\nOCR normalization & return\n```\n\n### 2. CANDIDATE GENERATION (`buildCandidates` - lines 441-605)\n\n**Pre-processing steps:**\n1. **Burst end detection** (lines 355-410): Skips initial garbled/short lines, prose preambles, and overflow markers\n2. **Hyphen-broken line joining**: Reconstructs lines split with trailing `-`\n3. **Short ALL_CAPS coalescing** (lines 465-508): Merges consecutive ALL_CAPS lines (≤2 words, ≤25 chars each) into single candidates (handles OCR fragmentation like \"LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS\")\n4. **Continuation line pre-merging** (lines 510-528): Merges lines starting with `/&+:(` into preceding line before candidate generation (handles \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\")\n\n**Candidate types generated:**\n- **Single**: Individual lines passing hard filters\n- **2-line**: Two consecutive non-empty lines joined (blocked if first is section label AND ≤2 words)\n- **3-line**: Three consecutive non-empty lines joined (same blocking rules)\n\n**Pre-filter to 25 candidates** (lines 590-602): Prioritizes ALL_CAPS, then short candidates (≤5 words)\n\n### 3. HARD FILTERS (`passesHardFilters` - lines 308-349)\n\nLines **must** pass ALL these checks:\n- **Length**: 3-80 characters\n- **Ingredient check**: No measurement patterns (cups, tbsp, g, ml, łyżka, etc.) and no \"to taste\" / \"do smaku\"\n- **Number start**: No lines starting with digits (with optional bullet)\n- **Metadata**: No serving sizes, prep times, categories, corrupted OCR serving (DLA patterns)\n- **Garbled**: Fails if suspicious (see `isLikelyGarbled` below)\n- **Cooking instruction**: No lines starting with cooking verbs (beat, fold, stir, bake, etc. + Polish equivalents like smaż, gotuj, pokrój)\n- **Pipe/slash/breadcrumbs**: No \" | \" or 2+ \"/\" (single \"/\" OK for \"TITLE / SUBTITLE\")\n- **Trailing page numbers**: No excessive spaces + digits\n- **Bullets**: No `[-•*]` prefixes\n- **Section headers**: No \"For the sauce:\", no trailing \":\" (unless \" : \" separator)\n- **Page references**: No \"Page N\" or \"Strona N\"\n- **Category tags**: No `[TAGS]`\n- **Section labels**: Not in SECTION_LABELS set (~100 labels in Polish/English)\n- **Single-word fragments**: No non-title words (the, and, for, but, etc.)\n- **Word count**: Max 7 words (or 8+ with separators: +, :, &, /)\n\n### 4. GARBLED TEXT DETECTION (`isLikelyGarbled` - lines 209-275)\n\nReturns TRUE (garbled) if:\n1. Fewer than 2 letters\n2. Pipe embedded in words: `[a-z]\\|[a-z]` (OCR artifact like \"Sp|aszcz\")\n3. Mixed Latin + Cyrillic (OCR corruption)\n4. Vowel ratio: < 10% or > 85% (English/Polish text is typically 30-50%)\n5. Single orphaned word ≤3 Unicode letters not in COMMON_SHORT set\n6. Single word with lowercase→uppercase transition (e.g., \"UuIw\", \"aBC\")\n7. Starts with lowercase letter (recipe titles never do)\n8. Mid-text sentence boundary: \". \" followed by letter (except if ends with \")\")\n9. Multi-word with garbled short lowercase word (≤2 letters, not in extended common-short set)\n\n### 5. EMBEDDING MODEL & SIMILARITY\n\n**Model:** `Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (Hugging Face transformers.js)\n- 384-dimensional embeddings\n- Pre-normalized (L2) so cosine similarity = dot product\n- See `/lib/text-classifier/embedder.ts`\n\n**Reference embeddings:**\n- `TITLE_REFERENCE`: \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\"\n- `HEADER_REFERENCE`: \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\"\n- `NOISE_REFERENCE`: \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\"\n\n**Similarity computation** (`cosineSimilarity` - embeddings.ts:30-38):\n```typescript\nfunction cosineSimilarity(e1: Array<number>, e2: Array<number>): number {\n  let dotProduct = 0;\n  for (let i = 0; i < e1.length; i++) {\n    dotProduct += e1[i] * e2[i];\n  }\n  return dotProduct; // Already normalized\n}\n```\n\n### 6. HEURISTIC SCORING SYSTEM (Pass 1-2, lines 824-937)\n\n#### Pass 1: Raw Score\n```\nrawScore = titleSim - max(headerSim, noiseSim)\n```\n- Quantifies how much more title-like than header/noise a candidate is\n- Can be negative (strong header/noise signal)\n\n#### Pass 2: Bonuses Applied\n\n**a) Position factor** (lines 892-895):\n- Multiplicative only (doesn't replace rawScore, amplifies signal)\n- Early candidates (relative position < 0.5): bonus factor = 1.0 + 0.12 × (1 - 2×relPos)\n- Later candidates: factor = 1.0\n- Effect: first candidate gets ~12% boost, fades to neutral at midpoint\n\n**b) ALL_CAPS bonus** (lines 900-902):\n- 2+ word ALL_CAPS: +0.08\n- 1-word ALL_CAPS: +0.03 (single words are usually section labels, not titles)\n- 0 bonus for mixed-case\n\n**c) Structural heading bonus** (lines 904-905):\n- ALL_CAPS ≥2 words where each significant word has ≥4 alpha letters: +0.10\n- Only applied to `firstStructuralHeading` (best structural candidate by rawScore)\n- Distinguishes \"AROMATIC SPICE MIX\" (title) from \"INGREDIENTS\" (header)\n\n**d) First-after-preamble bonus** (lines 920-937):\n- If all preceding lines were filtered/empty, first candidate gets +0.08\n- Handles cases like \"FISH & SEAFOOD\\nHalibut with Saffron...\" where section label is filtered\n\n**Score calculation:**\n```\nbaseScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus\nscore = rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus\nthresholdScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus (excludes structural to avoid inflating threshold)\n```\n\n**Structural heading selection** (lines 815-870):\n- Finds ALL_CAPS candidates with ≥2 words, all significant words ≥4 alpha letters\n- Penalizes truncated words (if \"FRON\" + \"SAFFRON\" present, \"FRON\" gets -1.0)\n- Picks best by rawScore, with tiebreakers: single-line > multi-line, more words, earlier position\n\n### 7. SPECIAL BILINGUAL HANDLING\n\n**Method 1: Embedding similarity** (lines 950-963):\n- Detects mixed-case candidate at position 0 + nearby (pos 1-2) ALL_CAPS\n- If similarity > 0.4, treats ALL_CAPS as translation → suppresses for threshold\n\n**Method 2: Layout-based fallback** (lines 965-978):\n- Mixed-case ≥2 words at pos 0 + ALL_CAPS ≥2 words at pos 1-2 with **no shared words**\n- Cross-lingual detection (e.g., Polish + Korean romanization)\n\n**Also handles:**\n- **Subtitle suppression** (lines 1026-1039): Short title at pos 0 + longer mixed-case at pos 1-2 → penalize longer by -0.15\n- **Mixed-case bilingual boost** (lines 1041-1080): Detects foreign name + English translation layout → boosts pos-0 by +0.15\n\n### 8. FILTERING & THRESHOLD\n\n**Threshold calculation** (lines 1082-1085):\n```\nbestThresholdScore = max(thresholdScore of candidates passing bilingual suppression)\nthreshold = max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7)\n```\n- Never below 0.08\n- Uses `thresholdScore` (excludes structural bonus) so bonus doesn't inflate threshold\n\n**Title-absent page guard** (lines 1106-1114):\n- When first 3 non-empty lines are all ingredients/instructions, require rawScore ≥ 0.10 and position ≤ 2\n- Prevents picking stray body text on pages with no title\n\n**Empty-pool fallback** (lines 1090-1104):\n- If no candidates clear threshold, pick first candidate if position ≤ 2 and rawScore > -0.05 (relaxed for early positions)\n- Or if position > 2, require rawScore > 0.02\n\n### 9. DEDUPLICATION & MULTI-TITLE LOGIC (lines 1116-1314)\n\n**Prefix removal** (lines 1116-1131):\n- Removes word-boundary prefixes of structural heading if heading itself survived\n- Examples:\n  - \"ARAYES\" removed when \"ARAYES SHRAK\" survives\n  - \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" alone removed when continued join survives\n\n**Continuation join protection** (lines 1133-1165):\n- Removes single-line versions of multi-line joins starting with `/&+:(`\n- Prevents \"& Coriander\" from destroying \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\"\n\n**Sub-section header filter** (lines 1167-1188):\n- Removes ALL_CAPS candidates followed by ingredient-like content if a longer candidate contains it\n- Example: \"CHLEBEK\" (substring of \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\") is filtered\n\n**Multi-line join protection** (lines 1190-1208):\n- When 2+ candidate words of a join appear as separate singles → remove the singles\n\n**Position-0 compound protection** (lines 1210-1226):\n- Removes distant candidates (>10 lines away) that are substrings of position-0 compound title\n\n**Deduplication rule** (lines 1228-1243):\n```\nKeep if:\n1. No other candidate contains it as substring AND is longer\n2. OR it's a compound title (has \" +\", \" :\", or \" & \" separator)\n```\nShorter wins when there's substring inclusion\n\n**Multi-title logic** (lines 1245-1314):\n```\nif ≥2 ALL_CAPS survivors:\n  if non-first are sub-headers (followed by ingredients) → keep only first\n  else → keep all ALL_CAPS (multi-recipe page)\nelse if 1 ALL_CAPS survivor:\n  if in last 25% of document → pick best earlier mixed-case (likely footer)\n  else → use the ALL_CAPS\nelse (0 ALL_CAPS):\n  if all survivors within 10 lines → keep all (genuine multi-recipe)\n  if span > 10 lines → collapse to one (body-text leakage)\n```\n\n**Final cap:** Up to 3 titles, sorted by document position\n\n### 10. OCR NORMALIZATION (lines 698-775)\n\n**Dictionary-guided OCR repair** (lines 647-675):\n- Maps digits to letters: 0→o, 1→i/l, 4→a, 5→s, ¡→i, €→e\n- Uses FOOD_DICTIONARY (~500 words) to resolve ambiguous substitutions\n- Generates all substitution variants and picks matches\n\n**Post-processing** (lines 721-775):\n1. Dictionary repair first\n2. Strip trailing section markers: `+ SERVING AND STORAGE:` → remove\n3. Character substitution (context-aware for ALL_CAPS vs mixed-case)\n4. Title-case conversion ONLY when substitution changed text (preserves clean ALL_CAPS)\n\n**Title-case function** (lines 611-625):\n- Lowercases small words: a, an, the, and, but, or, in, on, at, to, of, with, from\n- Polish: z, w, i, ze, na, do, od, za, po\n- First word always capitalized\n\n### 11. TEST FIXTURE STRUCTURE\n\n**Files in `/tools/title-loop/input/`:**\n- `{RecipeTitle}.real.txt`: Real OCR from recipe books (ground truth)\n- `{RecipeTitle}.generated.txt`: Synthetic OCR for coverage\n\n**Expected titles extracted from filenames:**\n- Strip `.real.txt` or `.generated.txt` suffix\n- Example: `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander.real.txt` → expected = `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander`\n\n**Multi-title syntax:**\n- Expected format: `Title1 + Title2` (space + plus + space)\n- Extracted format must contain all parts after normalization\n\n**Matching logic** (`titles_match` - lines 169-183):\n```\n1. Normalize both extracted & expected:\n   - NFC Unicode form\n   - Strip NBSP & BOM\n   - Lowercase\n   - Replace hyphens with spaces\n   - Normalize whitespace\n2. OCR substitution: 0→o, 1→i, €→e\n3. Strip Polish diacritics: ąćęłńóśźż → acelnosz\n4. For multi-title (expected with \"+\"):\n   - Split by \"+\", normalize each part\n   - Check if each part is SUBSTRING of extracted_norm\n   All parts must match\n```\n\n### 12. FOOD DICTIONARY CONTENTS\n\n~500 food-related words (no diacritics for OCR resilience):\n- **Proteins**: chicken, beef, salmon, shrimp, tofu, tempeh\n- **Grains**: rice, pasta, bread, flour, quinoa, couscous\n- **Dairy**: butter, cheese, cream, milk, yogurt\n- **Vegetables**: garlic, tomato, potato, carrot, broccoli, mushroom\n- **Fruits**: lemon, apple, berry, mango, pineapple\n- **Spices**: ginger, cinnamon, paprika, basil, oregano, saffron\n- **Cooking terms**: bake, roast, grill, fry, sauté, simmer\n- **Dish types**: salad, soup, stew, pizza, pasta, cake, dessert\n- **Polish entries**: kurczak, wolowina, ser, makaron, placki, pierogi\n\n### 13. TFIDF CLASSIFICATION (for tags, separate from title extraction)\n\nUsed for semantic tag classification (seasons, cuisines, categories), not titles:\n- **IDF formula**: `log(totalLabels / labelsContainingKeyword)`\n- **Score**: Normalized TF × IDF\n- **Threshold**: 0.2 for suggestion inclusion\n- **Similarity threshold** (embeddings.ts): 0.453\n\nLabels include:\n- **Seasons**: whole_year, spring, summer, autumn, winter (Polish equivalents included)\n- **Cuisines**: ~50 (italian, french, polish, indian, thai, korean, mexican, etc.)\n- **Categories**: ~12 (appetizer, soup, salad, pasta, pizza, rice, stew, roast, grill, baked, pastry, dessert, beverage, preserves)\n\n### 14. KEY FILES\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` | Main extraction engine (1361 lines) |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/embedder.ts` | MiniLM model loading & embedding |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/embeddings.ts` | Cosine similarity & embedding classification |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts` | ~500 food words for OCR repair |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/labels.ts` | Season/cuisine/category label definitions |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/tfidf.ts` | TF-IDF tag classification |\n| `/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts` | 30+ test cases (379 lines) |\n| `/tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts` | CLI wrapper for title extraction |\n| `/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py` | Self-improving iteration loop |\n| `/tools/title-loop/input/` | Test fixtures (~100+ recipes) |\n| `/tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt` | Accuracy tracking log |\n\n### 15. CURRENT ACCURACY TRACKING\n\nFrom `iter.txt`:\n- Iteration 1: 16.7%, Iteration 2: 16.7%, ... Iteration 13: 98.1%\n- Iteration 24: 83.8% (combined: 83.8%, real: 100.0%)\n- Iteration 25: 90.9%\n- Uses separate tracking for \"real\" (actual OCR) vs \"generated\" (synthetic OCR) files\n\n### 16. CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION NOTES\n\n**Immutable deduplication logic** (line 1229):\n```\n// DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" 5 times.\n// The tests require shorter wins.\n```\n\n**Structural heading detection** (lines 815-822):\n- Requires ≥2 words AND each significant word ≥4 alpha letters\n- Filters insignificant tokens (/, &, +, :, D))\n\n**Pre-filtering** (lines 533-542):\n- Removes metadata continuation fragments (short ALL_CAPS immediately after metadata)\n- Prevents \"N\" after \"SERVES 4\" from becoming a candidate\n\n**Truncation penalization** (lines 839-854):\n- Discards truncated OCR words with -1.0 rawScore\n- Example: \"FRON\" penalized if \"SAFFRON\" exists\n\nThis comprehensive system balances rule-based heuristics with semantic embeddings to handle real OCR artifacts while avoiding common pitfalls on mobile platforms."}],"totalDurationMs":97655,"totalTokens":143420,"totalToolUseCount":26,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1062,"cache_read_input_tokens":137561,"output_tokens":4797,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input