ting subsequent clean-looking titles as part of that same overflow block rather than valid recipe headers. The real issue is that OCR artifacts from adjacent pages are bleeding into the text, making it hard to distinguish actual recipe titles from noise. The system is performing well overall at 90.9% accuracy with just this one real failure, so I need a surgical fix rather than a complete overhaul. My best approach is the vocabulary corroboration check—requiring that content words from each ALL_CAPS candidate appear elsewhere in the document. \"DAT\" fails this test entirely, while legitimate titles like \"FINNISH MILK POTATO\" would have multiple supporting instances throughout the recipe text.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1901,"cache_read_input_tokens":49144,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1901},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"93fcd165-c384-4cf1-b48c-241fa9498df5","uuid":"25a98d64-49cb-4dba-a1f2-0940f4607c7f"}
